text: For a lone marketer (although hopefully hiring a new content person soon), what website tools (and any wisdom) would you recommend so I can 1) easily manage content updates on blog and core pages, 2) Use out of the box page designs/templates without crazy customization asks and 3) that makes on-page SEO a breeze. We are currently on Wordpress (and a custom theme that is 5+ years old and a beast to update). Would you stick with WP or look at a tool like Wix? Thank you!

elements.text: For a lone marketer (although hopefully hiring a new content person soon), what website tools (and any wisdom) would you recommend so I can 1) easily manage content updates on blog and core pages, 2) Use out of the box page designs/templates without crazy customization asks and 3) that makes on-page SEO a breeze. We are currently on Wordpress (and a custom theme that is 5+ years old and a beast to update). Would you stick with WP or look at a tool like Wix? Thank you!

text:
I'd recommend staying on wordpress and using a tool like Elementor to build your pages and create custom templates (I use it for my portfolio site and love it). Wix is notoriously bad for SEO, but I'm curious to hear if anyone else here has experience with optimizing content on other platforms.

You might also be able to hire someone (on upwork or by checking with contacts in your network) who can quickly format and upload content for you so you can focus on creating it, not managing it :wink:
